The paper deals with the problem of minimizing the average packet decoding delay in wireless network coded broadcast, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT) and wireless networking (cs.NI). The paper also presents a methodology for designing specialized approximation algorithms, which involves techniques from algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the complexity of the problem, which is related to computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the experimental study involves simulations and performance evaluation, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
